WEBVTT

00:09.240 --> 00:11.280
Let me show you what your father did.

00:11.360 --> 00:13.080
He blew up the Skanda pub.

00:13.160 --> 00:14.880
Alaric Henderson's confession
is on my phone.

00:14.960 --> 00:17.960
He said they had to talk
you off a bridge.

00:18.040 --> 00:19.600
Why did she lie to me?

00:19.680 --> 00:21.520
She was trying to protect you.

00:21.600 --> 00:23.760
When you get out,
anything you want,

00:23.840 --> 00:25.240
call me and it's yours.

00:25.320 --> 00:26.640
You should see the footage I've got.

00:26.720 --> 00:28.200
The Black
Sea in June.

00:28.280 --> 00:31.600
Holiday of a lifetime, until
something went wrong.

00:31.680 --> 00:32.920
-We don't have to lose.
-How?

00:33.000 --> 00:35.520
Theoretically, the voting system
could be hacked.

00:35.600 --> 00:37.920
Tell me that's another deep-fake
recording.

00:38.000 --> 00:39.800
Is this a joke?

00:39.880 --> 00:43.200
Made for women by men,
like the rest of the world.

00:43.280 --> 00:45.400
What was your role in the Skanda
bombing?

00:45.480 --> 00:47.240
I vowed to protect the union.

00:47.320 --> 00:51.280
I think you've done it!
Transfer of power at midnight.

00:51.360 --> 00:56.400
Give an unhappy woman some hope
and she is yours.

00:56.480 --> 00:58.120
If what you did, you did for the
union,

00:58.200 --> 01:00.720
it's done now,
so you can be honest with me.

01:00.800 --> 01:02.880
We'll discuss this in the morning.

01:02.960 --> 01:07.000
Dad? Dad? Dad! Dad!

01:10.080 --> 01:14.800
London 06:00

01:24.640 --> 01:27.800
Our newly won independence offers
freedom

01:27.880 --> 01:32.320
but with that freedom there comes a
challenge.

01:32.400 --> 01:37.000
Are we brave enough to take on
the challenge of independence?

01:37.080 --> 01:39.480
Do we have the courage
to write a new chapter

01:39.560 --> 01:41.080
into the
history of this country.

01:41.160 --> 01:44.520
Let's for a second draw
on our past.

01:44.600 --> 01:49.840
Our contributions to science
alone have been immense.

01:49.920 --> 01:51.760
Can you imagine
a world without Penicillin,

01:51.840 --> 01:54.320
televisions,
phones?

01:54.400 --> 01:58.160
Once again our voice can be heard
on the global stage.

01:58.240 --> 02:02.560
A voice for justice,
fairness and compassion.

02:02.640 --> 02:06.760
And for those of you already
condemning these ideas as unrealistic

02:06.840 --> 02:08.640
I don't blame you.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.680
Yesterday, it was unrealistic.

02:11.760 --> 02:18.880
But today we can make our
long cherished dreams a reality.

02:20.520 --> 02:21.920
Are you ready to make history?

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
Yes. Are you?

02:32.000 --> 02:35.000
The Head of Operation will meet you
at the power station.

02:35.080 --> 02:36.960
His name is Mitchell McGuigan.

02:37.040 --> 02:38.560
I have to wear this?

02:39.440 --> 02:42.320
Our GRU friends will affect
an electrostatic discharge

02:42.400 --> 02:44.520
causing a microchip burnout.

02:44.600 --> 02:47.520
The repair call to Rieper Hansen
will divert to you.

02:52.000 --> 02:53.360
This is the machine
you need to get to.

02:53.480 --> 02:55.200
First opportunity,

02:55.280 --> 02:57.920
type in the security code you got
from Torben's laptop.

02:58.080 --> 03:01.200
We insert the USB, type in the code,

03:01.280 --> 03:03.440
three minutes to upload and get out.

03:03.520 --> 03:07.560
Redback, 1,000 to one shot.

03:07.640 --> 03:12.160
But here we are.
This close to victory.

03:26.000 --> 03:30.000
Hey! Dad! Dad!

03:33.000 --> 03:35.000
Hey!

03:57.000 --> 04:00.000
♪ Piece me ♪

04:01.000 --> 04:03.000
♪ Together ♪

04:08.000 --> 04:10.000
♪ Piece me ♪

04:11.040 --> 04:14.040
♪ Together ♪

04:29.000 --> 04:31.000
♪ It's now ♪

04:33.000 --> 04:36.000
♪ Or never ♪

04:39.040 --> 04:42.000
♪ Piece me ♪

04:55.720 --> 04:57.520
Last night,
I spoke with the Heads of Security,

04:57.600 --> 04:59.560
Legal and Tech
and we are of one mind.

04:59.640 --> 05:01.960
The Scottish referendum was stolen.

05:02.040 --> 05:05.240
We must take every measure necessary
to reunite ourkingdom.

05:05.320 --> 05:09.400
Get your bots-blitzing social media
and all news agencies

05:09.480 --> 05:11.880
with stories
discrediting this result.

05:12.000 --> 05:14.920
Wait. That's not their job. We're not
Russia.

05:15.000 --> 05:17.520
We soon will be if we don't react!

05:17.600 --> 05:20.000
And tell the
Prime Minister I'll be there by nine. Go.

05:22.000 --> 05:24.920
Our job is to stop Redback.

05:25.000 --> 05:29.000
You think this isn't Redback? I'm
having trouble seeing a future for you here.

05:46.000 --> 05:46.920
Mr. Ogilvy.

05:47.000 --> 05:48.920
Thanks for this. Short notice.

05:49.000 --> 05:49.920
Take a seat.

05:50.000 --> 05:51.600
No, no. It won't take long.

05:51.680 --> 05:54.240
I've instructed the heads of
Technical Operations and Analysis

05:54.320 --> 05:57.160
to begin a full-scale investigation
into how a

05:57.240 --> 05:59.920
swing of the magnitude
you suffered last night was achieved.

06:00.000 --> 06:02.920
I'm sorry, you're... You're saying
the system actually was hacked?

06:03.000 --> 06:06.000
The final count was consistent
with the exit polls.

06:07.000 --> 06:08.440
I need you to make a statement

06:08.520 --> 06:10.440
challenging
the validity of the vote,

06:10.520 --> 06:13.520
instigate a moratorium
while investigations are carried out.

06:13.600 --> 06:16.000
Unless
you think the country should be scythed in

06:16.080 --> 06:17.720
half on the basis of a couple of exit
polls.

06:18.000 --> 06:21.000
By challenging the result of the
vote, we'd be risking civil unrest.

06:22.000 --> 06:23.920
I warned you about Redback.

06:24.000 --> 06:26.000
You didn't listen.

06:26.080 --> 06:28.120
Yes, we think Russia
hacked the system

06:28.200 --> 06:31.680
to rig the vote and then release the
tape to explain the result.

06:31.760 --> 06:33.920
-All I'm asking is for two weeks--
-Where's the proof?

06:34.000 --> 06:36.560
What? Well, that's what we need the
investigation for.

06:36.640 --> 06:38.640
You believe the system was hacked.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.720
Come to me with proof,
I'll give you two weeks.

06:41.800 --> 06:42.920
I'll give
you as long as you need.

06:43.000 --> 06:46.160
So, someone in this building
has facilitated a coup d'état

06:46.240 --> 06:48.000
and you're OK with that, are you?

06:49.000 --> 06:50.920
How fucking dare you!

06:51.000 --> 06:53.640
Special Branch examined the tape.

06:53.720 --> 06:55.440
They said it was recorded by
a directional mic

06:55.520 --> 06:57.200
200, 300 yards from here.

06:57.280 --> 07:00.560
You knew what was at stake.

07:00.640 --> 07:04.160
Why didn't you
just say the tape was fake?

07:04.240 --> 07:06.080
Because it wouldn't have been the
truth.

07:06.160 --> 07:09.840
Oh, the truth! The fucking truth!

07:09.920 --> 07:12.600
There are things more important
than the truth.

07:12.680 --> 07:15.680
I couldn't disagree more.

07:15.760 --> 07:19.080
Your naivety disgusts me!

07:19.160 --> 07:21.040
This meeting's over.

07:21.120 --> 07:23.480
Prime Minister, I implore you, I beg
you,

07:23.560 --> 07:27.800
go to the cameras,
declare the result void. Please!

07:27.880 --> 07:30.360
I believe in democracy.

07:30.440 --> 07:34.160
I work for the British
people. And, unlike you,

07:34.240 --> 07:37.400
I was elected to carry
out their will.

07:39.280 --> 07:42.840
The result must stand.

07:53.520 --> 07:56.840
You two... you don't even know
what you've done.

08:38.000 --> 08:42.160
Still here? Good. Saves a phone call.

08:42.240 --> 08:45.760
As you said,
you did warn us about Redback.

08:45.840 --> 08:50.080
Set up a designated team
to counter the threat.

08:50.160 --> 08:52.440
Then you allowed a Russian mole
to operate in the heart

08:52.520 --> 08:56.480
of this designated team.

08:56.560 --> 09:00.400
I've commissioned a judicial enquiry
into you and your department.

09:02.200 --> 09:06.160
I thought you should know.

09:28.000 --> 09:29.520
IDs, please.

10:04.840 --> 10:05.920
Go ahead.

10:06.000 --> 10:07.680
Thank you, sir.

10:42.440 --> 10:46.680
What you do today,
changes Europe for ever.

10:49.680 --> 10:50.600
Katrine?

10:51.800 --> 10:53.480
I'm in pain.

10:56.000 --> 11:01.000
There are a thousand ways to kill
pain. In one hour you can buy them all.

12:14.000 --> 12:15.000
It's mine.

12:22.000 --> 12:26.920
Thank you very much, sir. Thank you.
Good morning, sir. My name is--

12:27.000 --> 12:29.000
I know who you are. You're late.

12:35.040 --> 12:40.920
Hello? Hello? Look, I need to use the
loo. Can you let me out? Can you let me out?

12:41.000 --> 12:43.280
What's with the banging?

12:45.840 --> 12:49.000
Miss Ogilvy needs
to use the facility.

13:18.000 --> 13:21.200
The system your company installed is
barely two weeks old.

13:21.280 --> 13:24.520
Our CEO has asked me to
pass on his apologies.

13:24.600 --> 13:27.800
Our diagnostics have
detected a ergostatic surge.

13:27.880 --> 13:28.920
It completely burnt out your CPU.

13:29.000 --> 13:31.920
How long is this all gonna take?

13:32.000 --> 13:34.520
It's gonna take 30 minutes. In and
out.

13:42.000 --> 13:45.920
Nila, Tyler, Benny, Kita.

13:46.000 --> 13:46.960
Hi.

13:47.040 --> 13:49.040
Glitch will be fixed very soon.

14:41.600 --> 14:43.200
Whoa, whoa.

14:44.920 --> 14:46.240
Hands.

14:50.040 --> 14:51.960
Move

14:56.000 --> 14:58.920
Gonna grab a donut. Anybody want
anything?

14:59.000 --> 15:00.480
Staying strong here.

15:45.000 --> 15:46.280
Benny Sørensen?

15:48.920 --> 15:49.920
Benny?

15:50.000 --> 15:51.600
Ah, that's nice.

15:55.000 --> 15:57.000
You are talking about
Benny from Skagen?

15:57.840 --> 15:59.680
No.

16:03.000 --> 16:06.560
-Preben?
-Gunst

16:06.680 --> 16:08.360
What are you doing here,
Preben Gunst?

16:08.440 --> 16:11.440
Mitchell said I should say hello.

16:11.840 --> 16:14.840
Where are you from?
Where are you from, Benny?

16:23.080 --> 16:26.080
Kopenhem

16:26.440 --> 16:30.240
"Kopenhem"? You don't sound
like you're from Copenhagen

16:40.000 --> 16:41.000
Where's Tyler?

16:42.000 --> 16:43.040
He heard a doughnut calling him.

16:46.880 --> 16:48.800
Nice to meet you.

17:13.880 --> 17:15.200
Stop!

18:09.040 --> 18:14.000
Are you done yet? Is that blood?

18:18.000 --> 18:20.000
Oh, it's mine.

18:22.000 --> 18:22.920
What happened?

18:23.000 --> 18:29.000
You see, they took out the stitches
too soon. I told them this would happen.

18:30.000 --> 18:35.920
Nila, could you show Kita the
bathroom? There's a first-aid kit in there.

18:36.000 --> 18:37.000
Thanks.

18:40.000 --> 18:41.000
All right?

19:00.000 --> 19:00.920
Have you seen this?

19:01.000 --> 19:03.560
Adam's asked me
to polish his resignation speech.

19:03.640 --> 19:05.760
Do you think we should congratulate
Isla Robson?

19:05.840 --> 19:07.920
I think the less
we say about Scotland, the better.

19:08.000 --> 19:09.920
Scotland no longer exists.

19:10.000 --> 19:13.000
A message from Sir David.

19:13.080 --> 19:17.320
The 1922 Committee would
like you as caretaker PM.

19:17.400 --> 19:18.720
He says it's
unanimous

19:18.800 --> 19:22.200
and for some reason he's added '
a smiley emoji wearing a monocle.

19:23.880 --> 19:25.560
A symbol of royal ascent.

19:34.000 --> 19:36.000
I want Chief Adviser.

19:37.000 --> 19:37.920
Sorry?

19:38.000 --> 19:41.920
When you're installed as Prime
Minister, I'm your Chief Adviser.

19:42.000 --> 19:42.920
We've lined up a seat for you.

19:43.000 --> 19:45.960
Mm. In the Cotswolds. Fuck the
Cotswolds. I know what I'm worth.

19:46.040 --> 19:47.000
Nicky...

19:48.760 --> 19:51.280
You set me up.

19:51.360 --> 19:55.440
Digital voting?
Do you think I'm stupid?

19:55.520 --> 19:59.680
Do you think I was shocked when
the tape surfaced?

19:59.760 --> 20:04.120
Non-negotiable.

20:20.640 --> 20:22.640
Gavril.

20:26.240 --> 20:27.320
All is ready.

20:27.400 --> 20:29.960
Get comfortable.
Wait for the panic.

20:37.000 --> 20:40.920
Look at you. This is
a momentous day for us. Smile a bit.

20:41.000 --> 20:45.920
I will. I'll smile when William
Ogilvy, he is dead.

20:47.400 --> 20:48.920
You don't need to do that now, you
know?

20:49.000 --> 20:51.920
Oh, I do. With what I know,

20:52.000 --> 20:54.280
I mean, he's not going to let me
live.

21:06.000 --> 21:08.000
I've got a slight itch here.

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
You might have to give it a scratch.

21:13.000 --> 21:16.920
You see that? When I increase the
feedwater.

21:17.000 --> 21:19.040
Mm, the temperature went up. Do it
again.

21:21.040 --> 21:25.040
Oh, that shouldn't happen. Um...

21:27.000 --> 21:29.920
Show me.

21:30.000 --> 21:30.040
It's already--
Show me. OK. Give it two minutes. See
if it settles down.

21:42.000 --> 21:47.040
Oh, hi. You haven't seen my phone,
have you? I put it down in the kitchen.

21:49.000 --> 21:51.920
You've been helping Adam with his
resignation speech.

21:52.000 --> 21:53.920
Yeah. A line here and there.

21:54.000 --> 21:59.000
Maybe I could help you with your
acceptance address.

21:59.080 --> 22:02.000
I'm sure you'd wanna thank us for
rescuing you.

22:04.000 --> 22:04.960
Of course.

22:05.040 --> 22:10.760
You were ready to quit. The next Tory
leader in the gutter.

22:10.840 --> 22:12.760
What happened to you?

22:12.840 --> 22:14.840
You know what happened.

22:14.920 --> 22:17.320
I watched the Foreign Secretary leave
for that flight.

22:17.400 --> 22:20.360
A trip to the Black Sea.
God knows

22:20.440 --> 22:23.040
who came back.

22:23.120 --> 22:24.280
I had a breakdown.

22:24.360 --> 22:26.400
Why are you going on..

22:29.520 --> 22:33.840
Etta here
doesn't think I'm up to the top job.

22:34.000 --> 22:37.360
Either your friend is the king of
abysmal advice

22:37.440 --> 22:39.000
or he's been shafting you.

22:41.640 --> 22:43.920
The referendum was my idea, Etta.

22:44.000 --> 22:49.240
Yeah, and what I remember is this guy
bullying you to stick to it.

22:49.320 --> 22:50.320
Bullying?

22:50.400 --> 22:51.440
And then there was that

22:51.520 --> 22:53.840
fake-the-results chat with your
little accomplice.

22:53.920 --> 22:55.920
She only had that
conversation because you told her to.

22:56.000 --> 22:56.920
Absolutely not.

22:57.000 --> 22:59.400
And worst of all,

22:59.480 --> 23:04.080
you advise Adam to conceal Holly's
DNA results until after the vote.

23:04.160 --> 23:05.920
-I'm not going to.
-Zac, hold on.

23:06.000 --> 23:08.600
Which also somehow manages to get
leaked,

23:08.680 --> 23:12.000
which almost leads to Holly killing
herself, you little shit!

23:13.040 --> 23:15.000
What?

23:16.040 --> 23:19.000
The police found her on Westminster
Bridge.

23:23.000 --> 23:25.000
Why didn't you tell me?

23:26.000 --> 23:31.000
She didn't want you to know. She said
she wasn't going to do it.

23:34.000 --> 23:35.880
Well, I'll give her a call.

23:35.960 --> 23:40.360
I wouldn't. She doesn't want you
anywhere near her.

23:40.440 --> 23:43.080
Hard to believe, isn't it?

23:44.840 --> 23:47.120
When you're so
fucking wonderful.

23:58.040 --> 24:01.920
Hello? Holly. Where are you?

24:02.000 --> 24:05.960
I'm heading back to Scotland. Marcus,
I've done something stupid.

24:06.040 --> 24:07.960
What have you... What have you done?

24:08.040 --> 24:10.920
Remember you told me you were
investigating Zac Clark?

24:11.000 --> 24:13.000
Yeah.

24:14.000 --> 24:15.920
Well, I kinda borrowed his phone.

24:16.000 --> 24:19.000
-Tell me you're joking.
<i>-It's OK.</i>

24:22.360 --> 24:23.960
I... threw it in the Thames.

24:29.160 --> 24:32.800
Marcus, they completely used me.
Fuck them.

24:38.040 --> 24:43.920
Yes, we are aware. Yes. OK, will do.
Thank you. Bye.

24:44.000 --> 24:45.960
