24:54.000 --> 24:55.000
And rising.

24:56.000 --> 24:57.000
These must be wrong.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.040
We need to raise the control rods.
Shut down the reactor.

25:06.000 --> 25:09.400
OK, if it gets above 400...

25:10.520 --> 25:13.040
What the hell?

25:13.120 --> 25:16.840
Get that switched off.
Now!

25:29.000 --> 25:30.040
It's almost three o'clock.

25:33.000 --> 25:34.040
I canceled the speech.

25:37.000 --> 25:39.000
You're challenging the result?

25:41.000 --> 25:42.960
-No.
-Then why are you--

25:43.040 --> 25:50.920
I swore an oath of office. If they
want to get rid of me, they'll have to stage a contest.

25:51.000 --> 25:52.040
That'll take months.

25:55.000 --> 25:57.680
It'll take enough time for me to
persuade the membership

25:57.760 --> 25:59.920
that Zac isn't the right person
to lead the country.

26:00.000 --> 26:04.000
Me not trusting Zac isn't the same as
wanting you to stay on.

26:07.000 --> 26:08.920
The country's at a crossroads.

26:09.000 --> 26:14.040
Oh, for God's sake! Spare me the
speech. Why are you so incapable of change?

26:17.000 --> 26:21.000
People don't change, Etta.

26:24.000 --> 26:30.000
That's not true. I used to love you.

26:46.000 --> 26:47.920
The control rods are not responding.

26:48.000 --> 26:51.920
Try it again. Use the backup
generator!

26:52.000 --> 26:53.920
Nothing, nothing is working!

26:54.000 --> 26:57.920
Units 5 and 6 overheating.

26:58.000 --> 27:02.000
Shit. I
need to speak to the Minister for Energy. So, get him out of the meeting!

27:13.040 --> 27:15.000
Your father's back.

27:19.000 --> 27:22.000
How could you do that? What were you
thinking?

27:23.040 --> 27:30.920
If you do not have a belief that you
would die for, you do not deserve to live.

27:31.000 --> 27:32.920
What's happened?

27:33.000 --> 27:38.920
The Prime Minister... Fuck! I thought
we'd hit the bottom with Johnson.

27:39.000 --> 27:44.960
Look, why did you lock me up in here?
Huh? I'm asking you a question.

27:45.040 --> 27:47.040
I needed some time to think.

27:49.000 --> 27:51.000
So, now I can leave, can I?

28:03.000 --> 28:04.600
Miss Robson,
your Head of Operations confirmed

28:04.680 --> 28:07.400
that if the temperature on the
reactor continues to rise,

28:07.480 --> 28:08.880
you're six hours from
meltdown.

28:08.960 --> 28:11.680
I'm at the conference
in Scotland right now.

28:11.760 --> 28:16.520
Our state atomic energy board har
authorized any assitance you require.

28:16.600 --> 28:19.520
We have mobilized a team of science
advisors

28:19.600 --> 28:21.360
trained for this precise eventuality.

28:21.440 --> 28:23.520
I need your permission--

28:23.600 --> 28:26.000
How can you know what the problem is?

28:27.000 --> 28:31.920
We had an identical situation with
the same Rieper Hansen reactor in Sorgut.

28:32.000 --> 28:33.000
The EDF have offered help.

28:35.000 --> 28:43.000
The EDF... Do I have permission to...

28:55.000 --> 28:56.040
What did the Prime Minister say?

29:00.360 --> 29:02.960
He refused to challenge
the vote.

29:03.040 --> 29:08.000
He didn't want to allow time for an
investigation.

29:08.080 --> 29:11.920
Last night you didn't answer my
question. The bomb.

29:12.000 --> 29:12.920
Did I not?

29:13.000 --> 29:16.960
No, you obfuscated. You danced round
it. You didn't answer me, did you?

29:17.840 --> 29:20.520
Oh, well, yes, I gave the order.

29:20.600 --> 29:24.320
Well, I insinuated it...
I didn't think 11...

29:24.400 --> 29:31.000
God, no! But, yeah...
Down to me.

29:31.080 --> 29:33.800
And the attempts at assassination on
the Prime Minister?

29:36.360 --> 29:37.720
How did they hack Etta
Cornwell's diary?

29:37.800 --> 29:40.640
How did they get access to
those encrypted CPU calls?

29:42.360 --> 29:43.960
Dad?

29:44.040 --> 29:46.960
Well, that was an operation that was
always going to be a balls-up, wasn't it?

29:47.040 --> 29:50.440
I just thought
it would give, urm, Cornwell a boost.

29:53.600 --> 29:57.320
Do you know the Cold War
was won in this room?

29:57.400 --> 30:01.880
Strategies devised at this table...

30:01.960 --> 30:04.680
brought down the Soviet Union.

30:07.080 --> 30:10.040
And then the politicians came along
and allowed Russia

30:10.120 --> 30:13.640
to crawl out of the corpse.
Russia!

30:16.280 --> 30:19.760
Whose only intention is
to forge a new reality

30:19.840 --> 30:21.800
in which everyone loses.

30:22.000 --> 30:25.920
You have to make a statement to the
police and tell them what you just told me.

30:26.000 --> 30:27.480
Yes, of course.

30:33.640 --> 30:35.720
-Where are you going?
-I just need ten minutes.

30:35.800 --> 30:36.760
Why?

30:40.680 --> 30:42.680
I'm not gonna top myself if that's
what you're thinking.

30:42.760 --> 30:46.000
I need to phone the DG. Let him
know that you want a prosecution.

30:47.000 --> 30:48.840
Well, it's down to the CPS.

30:48.920 --> 30:50.960
No, no. This is what you want.

30:51.040 --> 30:54.280
It's
down to you.

30:54.360 --> 30:57.120
At least do me the honor of
acknowledging that.

31:00.000 --> 31:00.920
Make the call here.

31:01.000 --> 31:04.000
Ten fucking minutes, Beatrice, for
God's sake.

31:06.080 --> 31:09.760
News of a malfunction at the Gairloch
nuclear power station

31:09.840 --> 31:12.080
in Scotland is coming
in.

31:12.160 --> 31:16.200
Initial reports are saying the
reactors at the facility have lost the capability

31:16.280 --> 31:18.760
of pumping
cooling water into the core.

31:18.840 --> 31:22.000
If water levels
continue to drop,

31:22.080 --> 31:24.760
there is a real danger of a
nuclear meltdown.

31:24.840 --> 31:28.400
In an apparent snobb to the English
government

31:28.480 --> 31:30.080
First Minister, Isla
Robson,

31:30.160 --> 31:32.080
has accepted the offer of help

31:32.160 --> 31:33.920
from the Russian
State Atomic Energy Corporation.

31:34.000 --> 31:34.960
What's the holdup?

31:35.040 --> 31:38.920
Live from Inverness, we join Sabine
Mackenzie.

31:39.000 --> 31:40.920
This is the seventh...

31:41.000 --> 31:49.000
There's a bear in our back yard. Have
you spoken to anyone?

31:50.000 --> 31:51.000
Not yet.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.560
Spetsnaz boots. Military issue.

31:59.640 --> 32:02.840
Isla Robson's invited the Russians
to invade our country.

32:02.920 --> 32:04.760
Redback's final metastasis.

32:23.040 --> 32:25.960
The Russians are pumping in seawater
to cool the rods.

32:26.040 --> 32:34.040
Mitchell McGuigan. You can go. Go.

32:48.000 --> 32:49.920
Look, this is Scotland's problem.

32:50.000 --> 32:54.800
No. Regnum Defende. The Defense of
the Realm as a whole.

32:54.880 --> 32:57.520
Look, you were about to go to the
police and make a statement.

32:57.600 --> 32:58.920
I'm not letting you
walk away from that.

32:59.000 --> 33:00.920
Our country has never needed us more.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.000
No!

33:03.400 --> 33:06.320
Right, listen, this Skanda business
goes to court,

33:06.400 --> 33:08.080
you spend the rest of your life
in prison.

33:09.000 --> 33:09.520
I will?

33:09.600 --> 33:11.880
You set up the attack.
Used a suicidal agent,

33:11.960 --> 33:14.720
he survives, you hang it on Laird, he
gets away, you track him down,

33:14.800 --> 33:16.600
shoot him, make it look
self-inflicted.

33:21.800 --> 33:24.080
Jelena warned me not to use
Kelvin

33:24.160 --> 33:27.800
because she said it's too easy to
manipulate people when they love you.

33:27.880 --> 33:29.120
Isn't it?

33:31.000 --> 33:34.000
We are paid by the Crown to counter
by any means necessary

33:34.080 --> 33:36.720
those who would overthrow
parliamentary democracy.

33:36.800 --> 33:38.920
The Realm was
under threat, we took appropriate action.

33:39.000 --> 33:42.000
What you did, that was the threat.

33:42.080 --> 33:44.920
All right? People would be horrified
to know what you did in their name.

33:45.000 --> 33:47.520
The British public would stand up
and applaud.

33:47.600 --> 33:50.240
Would they? Well, let's take this now
to the police.

33:50.320 --> 33:51.920
All right? See what response you get!

33:52.000 --> 33:53.920
Well, obviously, I can't let you do
that now, can I?

33:54.000 --> 33:55.800
Because you know that you'll lose.

33:55.880 --> 33:57.920
Because we're at war!

33:58.120 --> 33:59.800
Oh, Dad.

33:59.920 --> 34:01.360
Listen.

34:02.520 --> 34:04.440
I need you with me.

34:06.920 --> 34:11.000
I want you with me.
You and me, Beatrice. We are a team.

34:15.720 --> 34:18.800
No, no.

34:18.880 --> 34:22.440
If you don't have a belief
you'd die for, you don't deserve to live.

34:22.520 --> 34:25.320
That's what you
said, isn't it?

34:26.760 --> 34:29.200
I would die for the truth.

34:34.040 --> 34:35.920
Made my decision for me.

34:36.000 --> 34:44.000
No, no. Dad. Dad! No, Dad! No. Dad.
Dad! No. Dad!

34:49.000 --> 34:53.360
Find Sergov.
Tell him to call me immediately.

35:18.840 --> 35:21.840
Gavriil, a favor you owe me.

35:25.040 --> 35:27.000
It's your address.

35:29.000 --> 35:32.000
Female. Thirty-seven.

35:35.000 --> 35:36.160
William...

35:36.240 --> 35:38.680
There are two guards. I don't want
them implicated.

35:39.640 --> 35:43.640
I never want to know any details.
Call me when it's done.

35:43.720 --> 35:45.160
You have that?

35:45.280 --> 35:47.000
Yeah, I got it.

36:13.000 --> 36:17.000
Let me out! Come on! Let me out of
here!

36:19.000 --> 36:23.000
Gavril, Beatrice wasn't
a part of the plan.

36:24.480 --> 36:27.160
I will do it,
but it is total shit.

36:27.240 --> 36:29.400
I will call you.

36:44.280 --> 36:48.400
William Ogilvy?
I'll help you get him.

37:24.000 --> 37:24.920
We need to talk.

37:25.000 --> 37:26.000
What about?

37:28.040 --> 37:34.000
Dead men who won't lie down. William
Ogilvy and Adam Cornwell.

38:08.120 --> 38:09.000
What is she doing here?

38:11.480 --> 38:13.560
We'll take care of her.

38:14.280 --> 38:16.040
Get a drink

38:16.400 --> 38:19.400
Wait for her father

38:20.000 --> 38:23.960
Why are you here? You've won anyway.
Won because you're insane.

38:24.040 --> 38:26.000
We're insane?

38:27.000 --> 38:29.920
You don't think causing a nuclear
meltdown is insane?

38:30.000 --> 38:35.040
I thought you were supposed to be
smart. We faked it.

38:37.000 --> 38:39.000
Who sent you to kill me? Was it my
father?

38:44.000 --> 38:44.920
So, you are smart.

38:45.000 --> 38:47.920
Hey! I want them both.

38:48.000 --> 38:49.920
She pointed a gun at me.

38:50.000 --> 38:52.200
Yeah, well but she actually shot me.

38:58.280 --> 39:00.680
So, are we working for William now,
huh?

39:01.080 --> 39:02.760
How much is he paying you?

39:05.000 --> 39:06.000
Katrine!

39:09.000 --> 39:13.080
Hey! If I wanted you dead, you would
have been dead.

39:13.160 --> 39:14.920
Drop the blade. Look.

39:23.800 --> 39:26.040
That's supposed
to make me trust you?

39:26.120 --> 39:28.080
You got anything better?

39:29.000 --> 39:30.000
Why did you kill him?

39:32.000 --> 39:32.920
He played me.

39:33.000 --> 39:33.960
Well...

39:34.040 --> 39:38.000
Yeah, imagine that. Trusting the
wrong man.

39:45.000 --> 39:46.000
Where are you gonna go?

39:48.000 --> 39:49.000
I don't know.

39:55.000 --> 39:56.000
Are you beaten?

39:57.000 --> 39:57.920
What?

39:58.000 --> 40:02.000
Well, you've been betrayed and you've
been used.

40:03.000 --> 40:03.920
I've been betrayed?

40:04.000 --> 40:08.920
I'm asking you... Are you beaten?

40:09.000 --> 40:12.040
Of course I'm not beat. Ask him if
I'm beat.

40:15.000 --> 40:18.000
OK. I know what we do.

40:46.000 --> 40:48.000
Something's gone wrong.

40:51.720 --> 40:54.920
I am honored. Scotland's first-ever
Prime Minister.

40:55.000 --> 40:55.040
General.

40:59.520 --> 41:01.960
Three-hundred men and women
have flown in to help you.

41:02.040 --> 41:03.240
They will need
accommodation.

41:03.320 --> 41:05.240
Three-hundred?

41:06.000 --> 41:09.320
Miss Robson, we have 26-billion
rubles in Scottish banks.

41:09.400 --> 41:11.920
England is intent on
destroying you.

41:12.000 --> 41:14.440
Our investment must be
protected.

41:14.520 --> 41:16.280
You need to close the border.

41:16.360 --> 41:18.800
No. Absolutely not.

41:19.040 --> 41:22.120
The sabotage of the nuclear plant

41:22.200 --> 41:25.480
was an act of war
carried out by your oldest enemy.

41:25.560 --> 41:28.920
If you don't close the border,
I will.

41:30.080 --> 41:34.000
But it will look
better coming from you.

41:55.000 --> 42:00.920
We were used. I didn't switch sides,
you did. I need to know why.

42:01.000 --> 42:04.920
Well, sometimes one lie makes you
realize that everything you said was a lie.

42:05.000 --> 42:06.920
What, and that's it?

42:07.000 --> 42:09.680
In ten minutes we walk into the bear
cage.

42:09.760 --> 42:13.520
If you're not 100 percent,
you're going to get me killed.

42:13.600 --> 42:15.920
That cuts both ways.

42:16.000 --> 42:18.920
You can't be thinking about what your
father did.

42:19.000 --> 42:23.040
Don't worry about me. I'm going there
to do a job and then I put him away.

42:36.720 --> 42:41.040
Madam Redback!

42:41.120 --> 42:43.520
If I were to give military medals

42:44.480 --> 42:47.480
you would want one.

42:50.000 --> 42:52.000
Did you hear about the Ogilvy woman?

42:53.040 --> 42:54.920
She wants to come home?

42:55.000 --> 42:59.080
When your father orders your
execution, things change.

42:59.160 --> 43:03.000
But, of course, that's... That's
your decision.

43:04.000 --> 43:05.000
I think I need to hear it from her.

43:06.000 --> 43:07.000
OK.

43:21.000 --> 43:27.000
She's here. She's talking to General
Groschev. Switch to video.

43:43.000 --> 43:45.000
Oh, my brilliant girl.

44:02.000 --> 44:05.880
-My friends, let's have a drink...
-To us.

44:05.960 --> 44:09.280
When powerful men set themselves
against truth,

44:09.360 --> 44:13.320
they must be stopped, no matter who
they are.

